Nintendo's "different set of gamers" is, and historically has been, basically about 20 million gamers in Japan. That's why they don't really care; they have at least half of them and it's enough for them. The 360 by comparison barely gets a look in.Valve's "HTPC" thing, though - it would have to be very cheap - very, very, very cheap. Something like Ouya, which incredibly actually seems as if it will be as promised, is pretty much all the HTPC anyone would really need - very cheap, natively connects to your TV, has a USB port and wifi for external storage, connects to any web-based delivery system you care to name.
