Posted: Sun Dec 09, 2012 12:49 am
The one thing that could potentially make it work, is the PS4. The PS4 is expected to use an AMD x86-64 (speculated to be "Jaguar" core based) with an AMD Radeon based CPU. Since Sony relied on OpenGL as a graphics target this gen, they'll probably do the same for the next gen. So basically, the PS4 is going to be an X86-OpenGL console. The hypothetical Linux-based Steambox would also be a X86-OpenGL machine. So there's a potential for a relatively easy additional target for PS4 devs.
